en_2647716_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – The cabinet has approved to increase the minimum wage in the private sector by Rs.
en_2647716_1	2500. The current minimum wage in the private sector is at Rs.
en_2647716_2	10 000 and with this cabinet approval, it would be increased to Rs.
en_2647716_3	12 500.
en_2647716_4	Non-Cabinet Minister of Labour and Trade Union Relations, Ravindra Samaraweera mentioned that the ministry would formulate required laws to increase the daily wage of an employee in the private sector to Rs.
en_2647716_5	500 from Rs.
en_2647716_6	400 as the Cabinet approval demands.
en_2647716_7	The minister also noted that the act is to be debated in the parliament for the approval.
